HEADWORD: Claque
<hw>Claque</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A collection of persons employed to applaud at a
theatrical exhibition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a group of sycophantic followers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

